# Cursor Entry

For `run issue ...`, do not use duplicated local stage scripts.

Use:
- `.ai/WORKFLOW.md` as orchestration source
- `.ai/PIPELINE.md` for stage details
- `.ai/agents/` for stage behaviors

Workflow stages:
1. Issue Intake
2. Planning
3. Implementation
4. Build (no tests, max 10 min)
5. Code Review
6. Test Authoring
7. Test Run
8. Branch + Commit + PR

Required logs per stage:
- Start: stage-specific emoji + `Start stage <n>: <name>` (table in `.ai/WORKFLOW.md`)
- End: `✅ Stage <n>: <name> completed`

Artifacts:
- `.ai/artifacts/run/MS-<run-id>-<stage>-<name>.md`

## CI Auto-Fix (separate from pipeline)

When the `tests` workflow fails, `.github/workflows/cursor-fix.yml` fires automatically.
It uses `@cursor/sdk` (Bun TypeScript in `.github/scripts/`) to launch a Cursor cloud agent
that analyses failure logs and opens a fix PR. This is independent of `run issue ...`.
Skill: `.ai/skills/ci-auto-fix/SKILL.md`

## Builds and verification

Before any build or CI-parity test command, read **`.ai/skills/build-via-task/SKILL.md`**.  
Use `task <target>` from repo root — never raw `docker buildx`.
